        ". Severn was one of seven children; two of his brothers, Thomas and Charles , became professional musicians, and Severn himself was an adroit pianist. During his early years he practised portraiture as a miniaturist.            In 1815, he was admitted to the Royal Academy Schools in London and exhibited his first work in ": null
